1
00:00:13,550 --> 00:00:15,590
(A restaurant in Seoul)

2
00:00:16,290 --> 00:00:18,960
(Why have the three siblings gathered together?)

3
00:00:19,260 --> 00:00:21,130
(We will send you on a vacation abroad.)

4
00:00:21,230 --> 00:00:23,690
(Congratulations on going on a vacation abroad.)

5
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:26,760
(The new youngest sibling who will join them, Kim Hye Yoon)

6
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:29,970
(How will the vacation of the four siblings go?)

7
00:00:31,070 --> 00:00:33,370
(This is a vacation?)

8
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:35,239
(This itinerary...)

9
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,540
(can be changed!)

10
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:39,780
(Was that so?)

11
00:00:39,910 --> 00:00:41,279
- This is it! - Right!

12
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,510
- Yes! - Yes!

13
00:00:43,110 --> 00:00:45,480
(I don't want to work!)

14
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:48,350
(After a desperate struggle to secure their vacation,)

15
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:51,090
(the itinerary for their trip abroad has been completed.)

16
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,759
(We did our best for this. Where are we going?)

17
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:53,990
(It's the Maldives, isn't it?)

18
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:56,590
(Where will the four siblings go for their vacation?)

19
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:58,960
(Bohol, Philippines)

20
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:00,160
(Gosh, hello?)

21
00:01:00,161 --> 00:01:02,370
(Screams can be heard instead at the peaceful vacation spot.)

22
00:01:02,930 --> 00:01:05,040
(The spectacular vacation begins.)

23
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:06,940
(The ruler of the mangrove forest awaits the four siblings.)

24
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,069
(The tyrant of the mudflat)

25
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:10,310
(Alimango)

26
00:01:10,710 --> 00:01:13,140
(Catch the alimango!)

27
00:01:13,310 --> 00:01:14,910
(I want to go home.)

28
00:01:15,380 --> 00:01:17,179
- Are you okay? - No.

29
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:19,520
(The four siblings get exhausted by the tough labor.)

30
00:01:20,350 --> 00:01:22,250
(After working for a while...)

31
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:24,690
(It's huge!)

32
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,430
(Jun Myun manages to make the first catch!)

33
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:30,589
(After Jun Myun's catch,)

34
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,760
(Dex also catches one!)

35
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:35,170
(Laughing)

36
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:37,940
(Try to catch one, Jung Ah.)

37
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:40,570
(It's my turn this time!)

38
00:01:41,510 --> 00:01:44,040
(Will the four siblings manage to complete their work?)

39
00:01:44,210 --> 00:01:46,080
I'll also look for one.

40
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,550
I'm Kim Hye Yoon.

41
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:51,180
The girl who has managed to make bread.

42
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,119
(She tries again with the same tenacity to bite on the bread.)

43
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,320
Let's poke everywhere I can.

44
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:57,589
Poke everywhere.

45
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:58,619
(She pokes everywhere.)

46
00:01:58,620 --> 00:01:59,620
Give it a poke.

47
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:01,660
Let's poke everywhere I can.

48
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:05,600
Why am I not hearing any sounds?

49
00:02:06,330 --> 00:02:08,170
I have to find one.

50
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:11,099
Hold on.

51
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,699
(She has been poking countlessly.)

52
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,610
(This isn't being replayed.)

53
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:19,340
Where on earth are the crabs?

54
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,580
(Going blank)

55
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:24,679
Where are they?

56
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,919
(Panting)

57
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:28,920
(Rage)

58
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:31,690
(She has been poking for a while while being filled with rage.)

59
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,360
I should go when Dex isn't watching...

60
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,629
and steal one from his basket...

61
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:37,930
to pretend I was the one who caught it.

62
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,299
This won't work.

63
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,600
(The bright character gets possessed again.)

64
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,300
What do I do? Gosh.

65
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:47,770
Hold on.

66
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,340
Hold on!

67
00:02:51,940 --> 00:02:53,580
Why are bubbles coming up here?

68
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:57,180
Look here. You see the bubbles, don't you?

69
00:02:57,710 --> 00:03:00,250
(She starts raking without hesitation.)

70
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:03,350
(It feels like a catch is near this time.)

71
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,959
(Hye Yoon picks something up.)

72
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,989
I...

73
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:09,430
(Did she finally meet the alimango?)

74
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:11,530
caught a cute clam, everyone.

75
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:13,460
(Peek-a-boo!)

76
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:15,230
(Has she lost it?)

77
00:03:15,670 --> 00:03:19,070
Why is a clam here? I just don't get it.

78
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,709
(While Hye Yoon is poking at the mudflat,)

79
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:23,710
Gosh.

80
00:03:25,510 --> 00:03:27,339
(Leader Yum is poking as well.)

81
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:29,480
(Let me find just one!)

82
00:03:33,950 --> 00:03:35,020
What?

83
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,290
(Did she sense an alimango?)

84
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:41,260
What? There's...

85
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:43,360
something here.

86
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,200
(Shaking)

87
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:51,100
(Her rake gets caught on something.)

88
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,569
(Did Jung Ah finally find an alimango?)

89
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,510
(She grits her teeth.)

90
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,580
(However, she doesn't manage to get anything.)

91
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,250
(I'm sure there's one here.)

92
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:06,749
(Jung Ah tries digging one more time.)

93
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:07,820
(Hitting)

94
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,250
I hear something, Jung Ah.

95
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,820
What?

96
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:13,720
Did you find one?

97
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,389
(Did you really find one?)

98
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:19,260
I can see its legs!

99
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,230
Is it there?

100
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:24,939
(The pincers can be seen slightly.)

101
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:25,940
Crab!

102
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:30,070
(She rakes even faster after seeing its pincers.)

103
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,080
What?

104
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,879
- Did you get it? - Is this a crab?

105
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:35,910
(Jung Ah, please...)

106
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:40,920
(The alimango reveals itself from the mudflat.)

107
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,820
- Did you catch it? - Yes.

108
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:50,729
(The alimango finally gets caught by Jung Ah.)

109
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:51,730
(Amazed)

110
00:04:51,731 --> 00:04:52,800
(- Did you catch it? - Yes.)

111
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,770
- Jung Ah caught one! - Yes!

112
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:57,199
It's so small.

113
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,940
(But it's so small.)

114
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:02,140
(It's small and precious.)

115
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:04,570
- She caught one! - I managed to catch one.

116
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,410
(It's a cute size that fits in one hand.)

117
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:08,810
It's too small.

118
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:11,210
Jin Young!

119
00:05:11,211 --> 00:05:12,719
(She still wants to boast about her small but precious crab.)

120
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,580
- It's so small, isn't it? - It isn't that small.

121
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:18,319
(They reach their goal of four with Jung Ah's alimango.)

122
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,960
We can leave now since we have four.

123
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:23,290
- Hye Yoon! - Yes?

124
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:25,000
We have four.

125
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,600
Really?

126
00:05:27,130 --> 00:05:28,329
Thank you.

127
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:30,370
(Choking up for no reason)

128
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:34,400
(They reach their goal of 4 in 2 hours and 30 minutes.)

129
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,810
I really want to catch two more.

130
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:41,480
We can get another coin if we catch two!

131
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:45,320
(Crab catcher Dex is still hungry.)

132
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,880
Can you give me the knife, please?

133
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:51,390
(Dex gets equipped with the knife.)

134
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,490
(This was filmed safely while being supervised by a local.)

135
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:57,729
(The crab hunter goes through the tropical rain forest...)

136
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:59,760
(while wielding his machete.)

137
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:03,369
(Let's hit another shell.)

138
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:04,430
Come out.

139
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,770
Look at Kim Dex continuing to search for more.

140
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,240
(I can't stand here watching.)

141
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,610
(The crazy siblings are back.)

142
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:14,379
At least one more.

143
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,610
(It's better to have more coins to change the itinerary!)

144
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:21,379
(He gives it his all to find another one.)

145
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:23,390
Where on earth is the crab hole?

146
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:25,960
Crab hole!

147
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:28,529
We've been around this area for too long.

148
00:06:28,530 --> 00:06:29,959
- It's hard to know what's the hole. - Right.

149
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,829
- It's confusing with our footsteps. - Right.

150
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:32,929
(It's hard to distinguish the crab holes from the footsteps.)

151
00:06:32,930 --> 00:06:35,100
I can't tell what the crab holes are.

152
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,400
Is this a crab hole?

153
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,770
Or is this a crab hole?

154
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:43,610
(Must we be satisfied with just one coin?)

155
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:48,280
Sometimes, the baby crabs live here.

156
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:50,610
- Sometimes. - Baby crabs? Sometimes?

157
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:52,249
Is that so?

158
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,480
(There are crabs between the branches as well?)

159
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:58,050
(He changes his plan right away.)

160
00:06:58,990 --> 00:07:01,390
(Find the crab trees instead of the crab holes.)

161
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:04,900
(Looking carefully)

162
00:07:06,330 --> 00:07:07,800
Gosh, he must've found another one.

163
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:09,370
What? What is this?

164
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:12,570
Is this not it?

165
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:16,140
(Little strokes fell great oaks?)

166
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:19,180
(He looks for the alimangos hiding between the trees.)

167
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,580
(Approaching carefully)

168
00:07:23,410 --> 00:07:24,710
Okay!

169
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,020
Isn't this it?

170
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:31,820
- A baby crab? - Yes.

171
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,320
Baby.

172
00:07:34,290 --> 00:07:35,590
Really? You got another one?

173
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,730
There's a crab hiding here.

174
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,400
(The crab appears.)

175
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:46,140
(Even a small crab must not be looked down on.)

176
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,670
Baby crab!

177
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:55,079
No! Baby crab!

178
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,080
(He misses the baby alimango.)

179
00:07:56,850 --> 00:07:59,620
(Tearing apart)

180
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,619
Grab onto this! There you go.

181
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:03,849
(It grabs the rake!)

182
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:04,959
There you go.

183
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,420
(Did you really think I would grab onto it?)

184
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:09,460
(An unexpected battle is happening in the crevice of the tree.)

185
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:12,530
(Dex looks for the crab hiding with tenacity.)

186
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:14,530
I got it!

187
00:08:15,530 --> 00:08:17,069
- Here. - Kim Dex is amazing.

188
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,230
(Another alimango is added.)

189
00:08:18,570 --> 00:08:19,570
Okay.

190
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:21,740
- He never disappoints. - Right.

191
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:22,939
Very good.

192
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:24,640
He's amazing.

193
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:29,410
(They can have 2 coins if they catch 1 more crab.)

194
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:32,950
(Jun Myun and Hye Yoon try their best again.)

195
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:34,050
Is this not it?

196
00:08:34,450 --> 00:08:35,550
I will go my own way.

197
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,559
We just need one more.

198
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,130
(They just need one more for an extra coin.)

199
00:08:44,530 --> 00:08:46,399
(Stopping)

200
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,400
It's a crab!

201
00:08:47,930 --> 00:08:49,000
Are you serious?

202
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:50,270
It's a crab!

203
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,169
- Are you serious? - Right. It's a crab.

204
00:08:52,170 --> 00:08:54,100
(The alimango between the tree gets spotted by Dex.)

205
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,469
It's a crab!

206
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,509
(I just need to catch this one!)

207
00:08:57,510 --> 00:08:58,980
Gosh, our Jin Young is amazing.

208
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,380
Hey, come here.

209
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,080
Come here!

210
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:06,550
Hey! Come here!

211
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,490
(Tearing apart)

212
00:09:08,890 --> 00:09:12,219
(The alimango is hiding in the crevice of the tree.)

213
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:13,390
I must get my hands on you.

214
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:19,400
It's a crab! I got another one!

215
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,260
- Really? You got another one? - I got another one.

216
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,399
I got another one.

217
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:25,470
(It grabs onto the rake with its pincer.)

218
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:27,300
- Awesome! - I got another one.

219
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,269
- He's amazing, isn't he? - He's not one of us.

220
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:31,370
- Yes. - Our Jin Young got another one!

221
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:35,110
- That's our Kim Dex! - I did it!

222
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:37,150
I managed to get another coin before the end.

223
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,350
You're amazing.

224
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:40,719
(Three hours have passed.)

225
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,889
(They managed to catch six alimangos.)

226
00:09:41,890 --> 00:09:43,189
- Let's go! - Let's go!

227
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:45,690
- Okay! - We have a long way back.

228
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:48,490
(How do we get out of this place?)

229
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:53,760
(Her legs have almost given out.)

230
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:55,569
(Her limbs feel heavy.)

231
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:56,670
Okay. Let's go.

232
00:09:58,130 --> 00:10:00,600
(The mudflat of the forest still slows them down.)

233
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:02,810
(Humming)

234
00:10:02,940 --> 00:10:05,440
(Their hearts feel light as both hands are full.)

235
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:06,939
Isn't this a crab hole?

236
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,579
(He's still looking while leaving the area.)

237
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:09,580
Is he still looking for more?

238
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,750
(Looking around)

239
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:15,319
(He naturally pokes at a crab hole.)

240
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,720
Isn't this a crab hole?

241
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:19,260
(He starts poking out of habit.)

242
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:21,490
(He starts poking as if he's possessed by something.)

243
00:10:24,730 --> 00:10:25,899
(He spills his bucket while falling down.)

244
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,400
No! The crabs are getting away!

245
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:31,700
(The alimangos get away.)

246
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:34,740
(He grabs one with his hand out of hurry.)

247
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:35,909
No!

248
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:37,270
(I can't let you go like this.)

249
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:38,740
(Groaning)

250
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:42,980
- Be careful. - It got away!

251
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:45,010
Look! It's huge! It's getting away!

252
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:47,180
- Over there! It went in! - Over there!

253
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:49,189
(I can't lose it like this.)

254
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,220
- Dex! - My crab!

255
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:51,860
It got away!

256
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,459
- It's here. - It was really big.

257
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,619
The crab got away.

258
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,089
(Struggling)

259
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:57,189
It's right here.

260
00:10:57,190 --> 00:11:00,900
(The tyrant alimango won't stay still.)

261
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:05,270
- Gosh! - This one was mine.

262
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:06,540
We have to get out first.

263
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:08,240
Let's get out.

264
00:11:10,610 --> 00:11:12,140
I think I see the way out!

265
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,310
I have survived!

266
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,210
Are you okay?

267
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:18,650
I should film a drama.

268
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,420
(Kim Hye Yoon's Cinema Special)

269
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:25,320
(Panting)

270
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:28,420
Did we make it out alive? Gosh!

271
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,830
We made it, Hye Yoon!

272
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,460
- Right. - We made it.

273
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,170
We're here!

274
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:38,700
- Help us! - We need help!

275
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,340
I see light!

276
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:45,540
(They're glad to see the streak of light.)

277
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,940
There's light.

278
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:48,909
There's light!

279
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:49,910
(They embrace the light with their whole bodies.)

280
00:11:49,911 --> 00:11:52,120
Are we out? What year is it right now?

281
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:56,290
It's 2023.

282
00:11:56,820 --> 00:11:59,190
How many years were you in there for?

283
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:01,290
What? We went back in time.

284
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,329
- What happened? - We went back in time?

285
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:03,330
Is that not it?

286
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,000
(Struggling)

287
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,399
(He kindly helps out his younger sister.)

288
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,430
Thank you, Dex.

289
00:12:11,070 --> 00:12:12,900
- Move inside. - You're so reliable.

290
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,770
(They get on the boat with their exhausted bodies.)

291
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:19,939
(She takes off her gloves as she takes her seat.)

292
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,239
All of the mud got in between the nails.

293
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,280
Right.

294
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:24,050
It's a mess, Jung Ah. It's the same for the toenails.

295
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:28,620
(The traces of their hard work can be seen right away.)

296
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:29,850
- Look at her. - Let's see your face, Hye Yoon.

297
00:12:29,851 --> 00:12:31,250
(Is Hye Yoon looking okay?)

298
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:32,820
Gosh, thank you.

299
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:33,820
(Affectionate hands of the eldest sister)

300
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:34,820
Gosh, that must feel itchy.

301
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,830
You get it now, don't you, Hye Yoon?

302
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:38,799
Looking pretty...

303
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,930
- won't last long. - She looks prettier like this.

304
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,499
- Right. - Did it last ten minutes?

305
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,500
Exactly.

306
00:12:42,730 --> 00:12:44,129
She looks prettier like this, and it feels more natural.

307
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:45,170
- She's pretty. - Right.

308
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,269
- Go home! Please go home! - Please go!

309
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,940
(It's time to leave the mangrove forest.)

310
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:52,039
We still managed to get it done.

311
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:55,280
(They head back after completing their first work session in Bohol.)

312
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:00,749
- Go home! - Gosh, Jung Ah.

313
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:01,850
I can't believe we went to a place like that.

314
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,219
It was no joke.

315
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:05,260
(They felt the worth of labor done with their sweat once again.)

316
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:06,990
Gosh, it feels refreshing.

317
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,859
I love it!

318
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:10,090
(With the cool river breeze that is blowing,)

319
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:14,760
(they cool off their sweat.)

320
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:25,140
(They arrive at the dock.)

321
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,480
We made it back alive!

322
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:31,050
- I can't believe I'm back on land! - We made it back!

323
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:34,350
Go ahead.

324
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:37,420
(Eyes of resentment)

325
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,719
Was this the vacation you all were talking about?

326
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,720
Darn it!

327
00:13:40,721 --> 00:13:42,090
How is this a vacation?

328
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:46,159
(It's true that they don't look like they're on vacation.)

329
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,200
Right.

330
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,369
You've all gone through a lot to catch the alimangos.

331
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:52,469
- Right. - How many of them did you catch?

332
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,540
We'll show you.

333
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:54,940
We need to count them first.

334
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:56,609
- Gosh. - Can we put them on the ground?

335
00:13:56,610 --> 00:13:59,040
(They get taken out from the bucket to be counted.)

336
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:02,050
One, two, three, four, five, six.

337
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:03,450
- There are six of them. - Right.

338
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:09,519
(The small crabs have been released afterward.)

339
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,919
There are six of them.

340
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,660
(We did well, didn't we?)

341
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:15,060
It was really tough. It really was.

342
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:17,159
Then, in total,

343
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,730
- we will give you two coins. - Two coins?

344
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,400
Thank you.

345
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:23,070
- Thank you! - Thank you.

346
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:24,869
- Go and get them. - Right.

347
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:26,239
(The treasurer hurries over to get the coins.)

348
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,000
Thank you! This is our hard-earned money.

349
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:30,539
- Make a draw right away. - Right.

350
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:32,239
(They draw a vacation activity right away.)

351
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,280
Please!

352
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:36,150
(Which activity will the siblings draw?)

353
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:38,180
A five-star foot massage!

354
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:40,580
- Okay. - I want the full-body massage!

355
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,650
Please!

356
00:14:44,690 --> 00:14:45,690
Please!

357
00:14:45,691 --> 00:14:46,919
(Their vacation activity gets decided by one draw.)

358
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:47,960
There we go.

359
00:14:49,090 --> 00:14:51,060
Let's get the full-body massage!

360
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:53,359
I will open it.

361
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,130
(Our exhausted bodies need a massage.)

362
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:59,770
(Will their wishes come true?)

363
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:05,880
(Please!)

364
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:08,280
Five-star foot massage!

365
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:09,879
- What? - Five-star foot massage!

366
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,250
(Screaming)

367
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:13,450
Are you serious?

368
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:15,119
Gosh!

369
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,219
(Greatly excited)

370
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,790
I'm getting a foot massage!

371
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:19,189
A five-star foot massage! Gosh!

372
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:20,990
(They got the activity they wanted.)

373
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:22,490
How did you manage to draw that?

374
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:24,060
Right. That was fascinating.

375
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:25,430
We have to get that next.

376
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,360
We should get a foot massage after enjoying a high-end meal.

377
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:32,470
- Give us the high-end meal coupon! - High-end meal coupon!

378
00:15:32,770 --> 00:15:33,869
We want it!

379
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,100
(Will they get what they want again this time?)

380
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:37,640
(Let's enjoy a meal out.)

381
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,579
- Local health food? - Local health food?

382
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:43,480
That is good enough.

383
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:45,420
Local health food.

384
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,319
Isn't it a creepy dish?

385
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,420
I'm sure it's not, Jung Ah.

386
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:50,219
- It's health food. - Right.

387
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:51,790
- That sounds great. - We got these two.

388
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:54,820
Where should we place these two?

389
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:56,589
Do we get a foot massage right away today?

390
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:57,790
- Yes. Let's get it today. - Today?

391
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:59,359
- We have to wash up. - Wouldn't that be a waste?

392
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,659
- It would be a waste. - That's too much of a waste.

393
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:01,899
- We have to head home as well. - But...

394
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,399
- you use it or lose it. - Hold on!

395
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,229
Use it right away. You never know what will happen.

396
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:06,269
(Make it happen right away.)

397
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,769
- Why are you living like a mayfly? - Gosh.

398
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:08,809
- What's with you today? - No.

399
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:10,469
- I'm serious. - You're acting like a mayfly.

400
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:13,079
In my opinion, it should be used after Dive into the Jungle.

401
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,639
That's when the five-star foot massage should come.

402
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,280
- Right. - Let's use it toward the end.

403
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:18,310
- Okay, then. - Right.

404
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:20,280
When should we try the local health food? Tomorrow?

405
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:22,249
The second day.

406
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,890
- The second day sounds reasonable. - Right.

407
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:26,760
It will be eaten as a snack before we cook.

408
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:28,259
- Right. - We don't know what to expect.

409
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:30,060
- Right. Let's plan things out. - Right.

410
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,529
You can get changed first.

411
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:34,000
- Sounds good. - Okay.

412
00:16:34,130 --> 00:16:35,600
You did well to draw them.

413
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:37,869
- You're the best. - You're the best.

414
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,400
- Right after we talked about it. - You're the best, Hye Yoon.

415
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,970
Let's see.

416
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,370
Let's see.

417
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:48,410
(Excited)

418
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:49,650
Cooling wipes.

419
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,750
- Would you like to wipe yourself? - I'll take one.

420
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:53,950
My neck is full of dirt.

421
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:55,690
- Me? - Me.

422
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:58,890
Would you like a cooling wipe, Jung Ah?

423
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,720
I'll wipe it for you. You won't be able to see it.

424
00:17:00,860 --> 00:17:01,860
Come this way, Jung Ah.

425
00:17:02,660 --> 00:17:04,630
- It's a cooling wipe. - Really? Thanks.

426
00:17:05,630 --> 00:17:07,430
- It's great, Hye Yoon. - Really?

427
00:17:08,830 --> 00:17:09,830
What's great?

428
00:17:09,831 --> 00:17:11,230
- What's great? - It's great to have an underling.

429
00:17:12,370 --> 00:17:14,070
(It's great to have an underling.)

430
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:15,470
(Annoyed)

431
00:17:15,471 --> 00:17:17,769
Oh, my gosh. Why would you think I'm your underling?

432
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:20,810
You're younger than me. You're a year younger than me.

433
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,410
I eat...

434
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:25,079
almost three times more than you.

435
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:27,020
- When were you born? - I was born on June 9.

436
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:28,420
What about you?

437
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,290
- What about you? - You're really older than me.

438
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,660
- What about you? - I was born in November.

439
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,220
There's a big difference.

440
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:37,090
Of course. That's seven months.

441
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:40,860
Was I the first one to catch the crab?

442
00:17:41,330 --> 00:17:42,370
Right.

443
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:44,470
I knew you caught one by the sound you made.

444
00:17:44,870 --> 00:17:46,239
It was incredibly thrilling.

445
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,940
I thought you were getting eaten alive by it.

446
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,040
You were screaming so much.

447
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:52,679
I've always been a laggard.

448
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,680
What do you mean?

449
00:17:53,681 --> 00:17:55,440
- I have always... - You're good at plenty of things.

450
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:59,480
You aren't saying more than that.

451
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:02,079
After a short break, I got...

452
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,149
- my appetite back. - Yes.

453
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:04,289
- I can eat now. - I'm hungry.

454
00:18:04,290 --> 00:18:05,290
Actually, I'm hungry.

455
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:06,490
Let's get going.

456
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:08,160
Hello? Honey.

457
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:11,060
Jung Ah is so affectionate. "Honey."

458
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:13,760
Since 6am today, we had been...

459
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,029
catching crabs in a jungle.

460
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:18,370
We caught crabs that live in the mud.

461
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:21,240
It was very hard.

462
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:24,909
Now, we're going to get some local Filipino food...

463
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:26,040
with the money that we earned.

464
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:28,079
Sir, it's very hard.

465
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,780
Jin Young is telling you that he's having a hard time.

466
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:32,079
You must look so cool.

467
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:34,079
- No. - He's very cool.

468
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,489
- I'm sure he is. - No, I'm not. Thank you.

469
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,319
- Honey. - Stay strong.

470
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,659
Enjoy your meal.

471
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:41,489
- Gosh, that's so sweet. - I know.

472
00:18:41,490 --> 00:18:44,790
I don't plan on contacting my husband for a week.

473
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:46,959
- Why? - Hand me his number.

474
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,229
I'll call him for you.

475
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:49,529
- I must tell him how you're doing. - Goodness.

476
00:18:49,530 --> 00:18:50,799
He just needs to know that I'm alive.

477
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,970
Jun Myun, please contact your husband.

478
00:18:53,140 --> 00:18:54,799
- Don't you agree? - Don't be like that.

479
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,240
- Once he knows that I'm alive... - He must be so curious.

480
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:00,580
Shall we play Hye Yoon's music?

481
00:19:01,210 --> 00:19:03,080
- Oh, my. - Connect to Bluetooth.

482
00:19:03,650 --> 00:19:04,850
I feel embarrassed.

483
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,119
- Come on. - My playlist...

484
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:08,049
Let's see what kind of music...

485
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:09,690
- you listen to. - Really?

486
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,289
- Connect. - The playlist is...

487
00:19:12,290 --> 00:19:13,290
(Which song will Hye Yoon select first?)

488
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:16,490
("JUMP" by BLACKPINK)

489
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,759
(The latest popular dance song plays.)

490
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,600
(Dancing)

491
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,470
(Feeling embarrassed for no reason)

492
00:19:23,670 --> 00:19:25,500
Is this the song you want to start with?

493
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,070
No, I just...

494
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,770
I played it to see your reaction.

495
00:19:30,010 --> 00:19:31,869
"Endangered Love" by Lee Chan Hyuk.

496
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:33,540
- Okay. - Right away.

497
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:35,309
- I mean... - Okay.

498
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:36,850
(I will play it right away.)

499
00:19:38,210 --> 00:19:41,950
("Endangered Love" by Lee Chan Hyuk)

500
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,120
This is your type of song.

501
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,960
- Isn't it nice? What do you think? - It's nice.

502
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:50,490
(Moving up and down)

503
00:19:52,430 --> 00:19:54,529
(It's here)

504
00:19:54,530 --> 00:19:56,730
(For real)

505
00:19:57,870 --> 00:20:00,540
(The siblings are here in the Philippines.)

506
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:04,340
(The deep blue sky that's full of clouds)

507
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,039
It looks like storm clouds are gathering.

508
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,349
- You're right. It might rain. - The clouds are coming.

509
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:10,909
It's raining.

510
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:11,910
(In an instant, the rain starts pouring.)

511
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:15,750
Mark, does it rain all of a sudden like this?

512
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:19,920
- Suddenly raining... - Yes.

513
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:22,189
(She brings out advanced English to communicate.)

514
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:23,990
All of a sudden? I see.

515
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:25,460
It's raining quite a lot.

516
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:27,759
- It's better that it's raining. - Right.

517
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,529
Otherwise, it's very hot.

518
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:31,799
Jung Ah, we never made kimchi jjigae, did we?

519
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,569
We couldn't make kimchi jjigae...

520
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:34,699
because we could never find sour kimchi.

521
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,839
That's why. You're right.

522
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:38,810
We couldn't get kimchi easily.

523
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,809
- Dex. - Yes?

524
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:44,080
- Is kimchi very famous in Korea? - What?

525
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,950
Is kimchi famous in Korea?

526
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:47,849
- Yes, it's famous. - Very famous?

527
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:49,850
It's very famous in Korea.

528
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,089
Kimchi is delicious.

529
00:20:51,090 --> 00:20:52,720
- Kimchi is delicious? - Yes.

530
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,690
(His mouth is watering.)

531
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:56,489
Mark says that he also likes kimchi.

532
00:20:56,490 --> 00:20:58,559
- Really? - Yes, Mark likes kimchi.

533
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:01,000
It's Korean comfort food.

534
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:02,369
(I see.)

535
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:04,500
What's comfort food for Filipinos?

536
