565
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,369
I feel a bit drowsy.

566
00:22:16,370 --> 00:22:17,640
- Right. - You know what I mean?

567
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:19,809
We chatted a lot on our way here,

568
00:22:19,810 --> 00:22:21,679
but everyone feels...

569
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,280
- Right? - I feel slightly sleepy.

570
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:26,079
What's famous here?

571
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,949
We should try their signature dish.

572
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:29,080
Menu, please.

573
00:22:29,990 --> 00:22:32,350
(Here is the menu.)

574
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:34,160
What's your signature dish?

575
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:35,930
This one. This is a soup.

576
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:38,659
Kare kare, sinigang with pork,

577
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:41,160
pork barbecue, and pork fried rice.

578
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:44,000
Inasal paa. This one.

579
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:47,240
- This one. And this too. - Okay.

580
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:49,270
(They're flustered by the pouring recommendations.)

581
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:51,170
I'll look up the name.

582
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,780
(Hye Yoon uses the chance to search the reviews.)

583
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:56,950
I don't know what "sisig" is.

584
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,049
Someone said that he'd come back to eat this again.

585
00:22:59,050 --> 00:23:00,779
I saw it in the back.

586
00:23:00,780 --> 00:23:01,850
I think it's this one.

587
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:04,749
- Isn't this it? - Gosh, it's so expensive.

588
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:07,259
We can use up to 2,000 pesos.

589
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:09,530
We should spend about 1,500 pesos here.

590
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:12,329
(How much...)

591
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:15,030
(is the food?)

592
00:23:15,130 --> 00:23:16,829
(Recommended dish in the review, sisig)

593
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:18,330
(370 pesos, about 9 dollars)

594
00:23:19,270 --> 00:23:21,069
All of these are expensive.

595
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,570
(On average, a dish costs 600 pesos.)

596
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:26,940
(An expensive dish costs over 1,000 pesos.)

597
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,250
Here's a mud crab.

598
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:31,749
(It's 390 pesos per 100g.)

599
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:34,920
(1 crab costs about 3,510 pesos.)

600
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:37,149
- It's too expensive. - What's that?

601
00:23:37,150 --> 00:23:38,150
(The dishes are too expensive for them.)

602
00:23:38,151 --> 00:23:39,889
What was the expensive dish?

603
00:23:39,890 --> 00:23:40,890
(Gloomy)

604
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:42,629
Here's what I think.

605
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:43,630
We should eat this much.

606
00:23:43,631 --> 00:23:45,060
We can order four garlic rice...

607
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:46,999
- Right. - and 4 that costs 75 pesos each.

608
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,199
We have to try the morning glory.

609
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,529
Yes, let's get some morning glory.

610
00:23:49,530 --> 00:23:51,229
Jung Ah, let's order one morning glory.

611
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:52,230
Shall we order a few...

612
00:23:52,231 --> 00:23:53,770
And 4 that costs 75 pesos each.

613
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,469
Really?

614
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:57,370
(Leader Yum who's been watching the younger siblings)

615
00:23:57,770 --> 00:24:00,310
Let's eat first. We'll insist later and use the credit card.

616
00:24:01,010 --> 00:24:02,749
- Should we just eat? - Yes.

617
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:04,310
Let's try all the recommended dishes.

618
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:06,480
Seriously?

619
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:09,250
(Staring)

620
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:10,650
Hye Yoon, you start.

621
00:24:11,190 --> 00:24:12,790
The first page.

622
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:16,260
Kare kare and fried jokbal in the back.

623
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:19,259
- Fried jokbal, kare kare. - Morning glory,

624
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:21,399
- sisig, rings. - Yes.

625
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,629
- Crispy pata. - Crispy pata.

626
00:24:23,630 --> 00:24:24,669
And pork barbecue.

627
00:24:24,670 --> 00:24:25,700
Garlic rice.

628
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:29,040
And karak karak.

629
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,510
Kare karak?

630
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,640
Kare kare.

631
00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:37,449
- Kare kare. - Kare kare?

632
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:38,909
- Kare kare. - She understood.

633
00:24:38,910 --> 00:24:39,920
One kare kare.

634
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:42,049
- And morning glory. - Yes.

635
00:24:42,050 --> 00:24:43,389
One. Okay, thank you.

636
00:24:43,390 --> 00:24:45,420
Are we spending all the money that we got today?

637
00:24:45,890 --> 00:24:46,960
Will it be okay, Jung Ah?

638
00:24:47,490 --> 00:24:48,490
How many?

639
00:24:48,491 --> 00:24:51,290
- The smell is making me famished. - Seriously.

640
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:53,699
Jin Young, can you take a photo of us?

641
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:54,759
Jun Myun, stop taking photos.

642
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,069
- Give it to me. - We should take a photo here.

643
00:24:56,070 --> 00:24:57,070
It's also raining.

644
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:58,070
When will we ever come here again?

645
00:24:58,071 --> 00:25:00,869
She's right. We should take a photo when it's raining.

646
00:25:00,870 --> 00:25:01,899
One...

647
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:03,910
Show the rain in the background.

648
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:05,809
You have so many requirements.

649
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:07,280
Oh, come on.

650
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:09,380
(The Siblings Are Waiting For Food)

651
00:25:09,510 --> 00:25:12,210
Jun Myun makes souvenirs for us.

652
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:13,380
Of course.

653
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:14,579
It looks great.

654
00:25:14,580 --> 00:25:15,580
(Satisfied)

655
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,119
"Gosh, your shoes are very small."

656
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:19,560
- That's what they said. - This is sisig with egg.

657
00:25:19,990 --> 00:25:22,630
(The first dish grabs their attention.)

658
00:25:24,230 --> 00:25:26,900
(Savory pork topped with a simple, light egg)

659
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,929
- It looks very good. - It looks delicious.

660
00:25:29,930 --> 00:25:31,000
(The first dish, sisig with egg)

661
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:32,869
- This is barbecue. - Okay.

662
00:25:32,870 --> 00:25:34,440
(Food keeps being served.)

663
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:36,669
- Kare kare? - Is this kare kare?

664
00:25:36,670 --> 00:25:37,670
Gosh, the smell.

665
00:25:37,910 --> 00:25:39,840
It would taste good with fried rice.

666
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:44,510
(A peanut-based Filipino stew made with oxtail and vegetables)

667
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:48,580
(The second dish, kare kare)

668
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,220
Gosh, we ordered a lot.

669
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,760
Here you go.

670
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:53,889
Let's put this in the middle.

671
00:25:53,890 --> 00:25:55,289
This is the main dish.

672
00:25:55,290 --> 00:25:56,290
(The main dish, crispy pata)

673
00:25:57,590 --> 00:26:00,360
(A signature Filipino party dish of crispy fried pork feet)

674
00:26:00,860 --> 00:26:03,600
(Featuring sour onion sauce)

675
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,370
Here's your morning glory.

676
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:06,999
(They meet their favorite dish.)

677
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,040
Morning glory.

678
00:26:08,140 --> 00:26:10,340
Is this what morning glory looks like?

679
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:15,010
(Filipinos' comfort food, stir-fried morning glory)

680
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:17,949
- Bon appetit. - Bon appetit.

681
00:26:17,950 --> 00:26:19,180
What should I start with?

682
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:21,850
I'll start with this. I wanted to try it.

683
00:26:22,750 --> 00:26:23,750
Go ahead and eat.

684
00:26:24,690 --> 00:26:26,019
Help yourselves.

685
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,520
You told us to order a lot.

686
00:26:27,620 --> 00:26:28,689
I did.

687
00:26:28,690 --> 00:26:31,490
(How does it taste?)

688
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:34,300
(Humming)

689
00:26:34,430 --> 00:26:35,560
Jin Young, do you want some kare kare?

690
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:37,669
Yes, just a little for tasting.

691
00:26:37,670 --> 00:26:39,370
A little? Here you go.

692
00:26:39,670 --> 00:26:40,800
- Thank you. - Thank you.

693
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:42,370
Hye Yoon.

694
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,840
(One serving for Hye Yoon)

695
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:48,040
(A bite of kare kare)

696
00:26:48,780 --> 00:26:51,180
(Hye Yoon also tries it.)

697
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:53,980
(She takes a spoon of rice immediately.)

698
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,620
(An explosion of savory taste)

699
00:26:56,190 --> 00:26:58,550
- It's delicious. - Yes, it's good.

700
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:02,560
- It suits my taste. - Yes.

701
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:04,430
Me too.

702
00:27:05,090 --> 00:27:06,130
Everything is slightly salty.

703
00:27:07,060 --> 00:27:08,660
The chicken is really delicious.

704
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,830
I don't think it's chicken.

705
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:12,300
- It's not chicken? - Isn't it pork?

706
00:27:12,301 --> 00:27:13,339
It's jokbal.

707
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:14,440
(Fried jokbal that's as crispy as chicken)

708
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,970
(Trying it with the sour onion sauce)

709
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:20,840
(Crunch)

710
00:27:21,610 --> 00:27:22,950
- Did you eat this? - Yes.

711
00:27:23,310 --> 00:27:24,350
Jung Ah.

712
00:27:25,150 --> 00:27:26,379
- Is that good? - It's delicious.

713
00:27:26,380 --> 00:27:28,419
Try the piece...

714
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:29,850
- with some skin. - Try this too.

715
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:33,690
(Fried jokbal that's perfect for the Korean palate)

716
00:27:34,390 --> 00:27:36,430
Try this. It's very delicious.

717
00:27:36,690 --> 00:27:37,830
It's crispy.

718
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:41,060
(Dex tries a bite on top of the garlic rice.)

719
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:44,130
(Jokbal tastes the best when you tear it with both hands.)

720
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,670
(Eating)

721
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:49,970
(Staring)

722
00:27:50,070 --> 00:27:51,440
You seem to enjoy it.

723
00:27:51,870 --> 00:27:54,680
It's tasty. It's seasoned perfectly for my taste.

724
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:57,450
Which dish do you like the best?

725
00:27:59,050 --> 00:28:00,349
- This. - Is that good?

726
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:02,320
You like that? I like this one.

727
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:07,690
(Tearing and enjoying every bite)

728
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:10,489
The food is generally salty,

729
00:28:10,490 --> 00:28:13,060
- so it increases my appetite. - Yes, it's delicious.

730
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,759
It's so big that it looks overwhelming.

731
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:18,000
(Hye Yoon tries sisig that was recommended in the reviews.)

732
00:28:18,700 --> 00:28:21,199
(Will it be delicious like the review said?)

733
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,970
(Humming)

734
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:26,980
(Dex also takes a bite with rice.)

735
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:28,810
(Crunch)

736
00:28:29,340 --> 00:28:30,710
Is there mayonnaise in it?

737
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:33,379
It's exotic,

738
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:35,219
yet it suits our taste perfectly.

739
00:28:35,220 --> 00:28:37,020
- It's not completely foreign. - Right.

740
00:28:38,190 --> 00:28:41,059
(A Filipino dish that goes well with rice)

741
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:42,190
It's delicious.

742
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:47,100
It'd be perfect with some kimchi.

743
00:28:47,260 --> 00:28:48,329
- Yes. - Right.

744
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:49,499
I agree.

745
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:52,500
When you crave kimchi, have some morning glory.

746
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,400
(Roll it around on the spoon.)

747
00:28:55,670 --> 00:28:57,640
(Taking a bite neatly)

748
00:28:59,210 --> 00:29:01,780
(The second eldest takes a generous amount.)

749
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:05,710
(Taking a mouthful with indulgence)

750
00:29:07,050 --> 00:29:10,349
(Like the older sisters, the youngest slurps morning glory.)

751
00:29:10,350 --> 00:29:12,990
(Humming)

752
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:14,560
It's good.

753
00:29:15,890 --> 00:29:16,929
It's very good.

754
00:29:16,930 --> 00:29:19,460
(Slurping one more time)

755
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:25,030
(They were so caught up in eating.)

756
00:29:25,670 --> 00:29:27,840
(The plates become empty before they know it.)

757
00:29:28,140 --> 00:29:30,710
I should finish it. It's so tasty.

758
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:32,369
It's impossible to eat here...

759
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:33,640
- without morning glory. - Morning glory.

760
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,540
- Hye Yoon. - It's impossible to eat.

761
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:37,550
Let's buy a bundle of it and stir-fry it.

762
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:39,150
- I'd love that. - Every day...

763
00:29:39,151 --> 00:29:41,480
- Jung Ah, let's buy some fruit. - Fructose.

764
00:29:42,250 --> 00:29:44,119
We're in the Philippines, so let's get some fruit.

765
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,589
- That sounds great. - What's with the look?

766
00:29:45,590 --> 00:29:46,659
- I want some fruit. - On my list,

767
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:48,159
there's no fruit.

768
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:50,789
- Fruit is a must on my list. - Oh, my gosh.

769
00:29:50,790 --> 00:29:52,489
Jung Ah, we're in the Philippines.

770
00:29:52,490 --> 00:29:53,959
- We should have some fruit. - Definitely.

771
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,059
Let's have some mangoes.

772
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:56,670
- I agree. - There are so many mangoes.

773
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:59,000
Why would you eat that? It's sweet.

774
00:29:59,330 --> 00:30:02,840
It's refreshing, crunchy, and delicious.

775
00:30:03,140 --> 00:30:05,670
- I'd love to devour it. - It'd be refreshing.

776
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,410
I was the first to catch a crab today.

777
00:30:08,980 --> 00:30:10,249
- Okay. - Throughout all three seasons,

778
00:30:10,250 --> 00:30:11,509
I pulled off something big.

779
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:12,680
But that's...

780
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:14,549
- You're right. - Be generous with me,

781
00:30:14,550 --> 00:30:16,050
- Jung Ah. - Let's celebrate.

782
00:30:16,890 --> 00:30:19,989
Now that we're almost done, I'm a little worried...

783
00:30:19,990 --> 00:30:21,960
as the treasurer. I have to admit.

784
00:30:22,820 --> 00:30:24,830
We can earn more money later.

785
00:30:25,390 --> 00:30:26,660
We have to work.

786
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,870
- Thank you for the food. - Thank you for the food.

787
00:30:30,930 --> 00:30:34,100
(The siblings go in somewhere after leaving the restaurant.)

788
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:37,870
(A small, local supermarket next to the restaurant)

789
00:30:39,010 --> 00:30:45,410
(A paradise of diverse and fresh fruits)

790
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:48,820
(Clusters of bananas hanging)

791
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,820
(Heaps of yellow mangoes)

792
00:30:52,990 --> 00:30:56,660
