Amazing.

2340
01:33:23,299 --> 01:33:25,538
- I think you underestimated us. - There's nothing we're bad at.

2341
01:33:25,539 --> 01:33:26,639
(The two sisters' game-playing skills were underestimated.)

2342
01:33:26,969 --> 01:33:28,308
- Treasurer Kim. - Treasurer Kim.

2343
01:33:28,309 --> 01:33:29,338
Yes.

2344
01:33:29,339 --> 01:33:30,509
- Put in the coin. - Okay.

2345
01:33:30,679 --> 01:33:31,938
- Should I go ahead? - Yes.

2346
01:33:31,939 --> 01:33:33,209
Hye Yoon's good at this.

2347
01:33:33,439 --> 01:33:35,509
Really? I don't do much.

2348
01:33:35,849 --> 01:33:36,879
Please.

2349
01:33:37,449 --> 01:33:38,518
Let's go.

2350
01:33:38,519 --> 01:33:40,218
- I have a good feeling. - Hye Yoon's good at this.

2351
01:33:40,219 --> 01:33:41,749
Just don't draw "No prize."

2352
01:33:42,189 --> 01:33:43,219
Okay.

2353
01:33:43,819 --> 01:33:45,659
(She drew their first capsule.)

2354
01:33:46,289 --> 01:33:48,259
There's actually something I'm hoping for.

2355
01:33:48,359 --> 01:33:49,389
What is it?

2356
01:33:49,789 --> 01:33:51,959
- The high-end meal coupon. - The high-end meal coupon.

2357
01:33:52,129 --> 01:33:53,329
I want the full-body massage coupon.

2358
01:33:54,169 --> 01:33:55,169
The high-end meal coupon and...

2359
01:33:55,169 --> 01:33:56,169
- the full-body massage coupon? - I want the company card perk.

2360
01:33:56,170 --> 01:33:57,469
I actually want the company card perk.

2361
01:33:58,269 --> 01:33:59,938
The company card perk can actually cover everything,

2362
01:33:59,939 --> 01:34:03,409
including high-end meals. We can do all these things.

2363
01:34:03,569 --> 01:34:05,408
I think what I drew isn't bad.

2364
01:34:05,409 --> 01:34:07,408
I caught a glimpse of what it is.

2365
01:34:07,409 --> 01:34:08,449
What is it?

2366
01:34:10,279 --> 01:34:12,679
- "At-home cafe unlocked." - At-home cafe.

2367
01:34:13,019 --> 01:34:14,818
In the morning, we...

2368
01:34:14,819 --> 01:34:16,289
Are we going somewhere to get brunch?

2369
01:34:16,749 --> 01:34:20,488
We're providing you with a coffee machine like you wanted.

2370
01:34:20,489 --> 01:34:22,459
(They'll be provided with a coffee machine.)

2371
01:34:22,929 --> 01:34:25,059
You're setting up a coffee machine here?

2372
01:34:25,199 --> 01:34:27,069
Hye Yoon and I are the only ones who drink coffee.

2373
01:34:27,799 --> 01:34:30,469
I don't drink coffee anymore.

2374
01:34:30,999 --> 01:34:33,198
I only had one earlier to wake myself up.

2375
01:34:33,199 --> 01:34:34,639
Jun Myun, your eyes are about to bulge out.

2376
01:34:34,869 --> 01:34:36,838
- Should I take them if they fall? - Yes, take them.

2377
01:34:36,839 --> 01:34:38,209
- They were about to fall right out. - Got it.

2378
01:34:38,279 --> 01:34:40,209
- All right, we'll drink coffee. - Good.

2379
01:34:40,549 --> 01:34:41,949
- Let's see the next one. - Okay.

2380
01:34:42,379 --> 01:34:43,578
- I'll turn the lever. - Okay.

2381
01:34:43,579 --> 01:34:44,749
Turn it!

2382
01:34:46,049 --> 01:34:48,519
(She drew their second capsule.)

2383
01:34:48,789 --> 01:34:50,319
Please.

2384
01:34:51,559 --> 01:34:53,858
(The second item to be added on their schedule is...)

2385
01:34:53,859 --> 01:34:55,088
- Nice. - The local market pass.

2386
01:34:55,089 --> 01:34:57,858
- The local market. - We can get anything there, right?

2387
01:34:57,859 --> 01:34:59,729
Yes, when you buy groceries there.

2388
01:35:00,869 --> 01:35:02,198
- That's good. - This is a big one.

2389
01:35:02,199 --> 01:35:05,239
(They can buy an unlimited amount of fresh local ingredients.)

2390
01:35:06,899 --> 01:35:09,139
When should we go to the local market?

2391
01:35:09,839 --> 01:35:11,009
The market...

2392
01:35:11,179 --> 01:35:13,279
Should we go after work?

2393
01:35:13,379 --> 01:35:15,978
We'll work, get groceries, come home and cook.

2394
01:35:15,979 --> 01:35:17,619
(Day 3, when they have nothing besides work on their schedule?)

2395
01:35:17,719 --> 01:35:18,848
We'll work and...

2396
01:35:18,849 --> 01:35:20,718
(They decide to go to the local market on Day 3.)

2397
01:35:20,719 --> 01:35:21,988
- You're fine with this, right? - Yes, that's fine.

2398
01:35:21,989 --> 01:35:23,718
It's decided then. We did good today.

2399
01:35:23,719 --> 01:35:25,589
We'll be back next time.

2400
01:35:26,759 --> 01:35:27,958
She said, "I'll be back."

2401
01:35:27,959 --> 01:35:29,529
(The Fresh Off the Sea Vacation Schedule Games will continue.)

2402
01:35:29,589 --> 01:35:31,799
I wonder why we're so good at playing games.

2403
01:35:32,299 --> 01:35:34,129
We have zero intention of losing a game.

2404
01:35:35,099 --> 01:35:36,769
- Are you going to drink? - Yes.

2405
01:35:37,099 --> 01:35:38,769
- Can you bring him a glass? - Okay.

2406
01:35:39,339 --> 01:35:40,769
We've already been drinking.

2407
01:35:42,869 --> 01:35:45,108
Dex, you should come here.

2408
01:35:45,109 --> 01:35:46,679
I can't reach the glass.

2409
01:35:48,709 --> 01:35:49,849
Gosh, that's sad.

2410
01:35:50,679 --> 01:35:53,048
- I couldn't see the glasses. - How cute.

2411
01:35:53,049 --> 01:35:54,389
I didn't want to make a mistake.

2412
01:35:56,319 --> 01:35:59,689
We'll just wake up in the morning and dance with the turtles.

2413
01:36:00,889 --> 01:36:01,928
What?

2414
01:36:01,929 --> 01:36:04,498
We'll wake up in the morning and dance?

2415
01:36:04,499 --> 01:36:05,629
(It's frustrating to think about dancing with turtles.)

2416
01:36:06,359 --> 01:36:08,829
Just think of it as an aerobic workout in the morning.

2417
01:36:09,469 --> 01:36:11,039
I think it's hopping.

2418
01:36:11,869 --> 01:36:13,168
I'm starting to get worried.

2419
01:36:13,169 --> 01:36:14,169
(During dinner a while ago)

2420
01:36:14,169 --> 01:36:15,169
What could it be?

2421
01:36:15,170 --> 01:36:16,768
(Curious)

2422
01:36:16,769 --> 01:36:18,538
We might find out if we look it up.

2423
01:36:18,539 --> 01:36:20,179
Ask your friend.

2424
01:36:20,749 --> 01:36:22,749
Was it Gemini?

2425
01:36:23,249 --> 01:36:24,779
(Rummaging)

2426
01:36:25,549 --> 01:36:28,119
(Will Gemini know the answer?)

2427
01:36:28,349 --> 01:36:29,349
(Typing)

2428
01:36:31,259 --> 01:36:33,718
(The hopping tour is a way to dance with the turtles.)

2429
01:36:33,719 --> 01:36:34,788
(Hopping tour)

2430
01:36:34,789 --> 01:36:35,829
"Hopping tour?"

2431
01:36:36,329 --> 01:36:38,029
This is what a hopping tour is like.

2432
01:36:38,559 --> 01:36:39,759
What's a hopping tour?

2433
01:36:40,329 --> 01:36:43,328
A bunch of people get on the same boat.

2434
01:36:43,329 --> 01:36:45,698
The boat reaches a certain spot,

2435
01:36:45,699 --> 01:36:48,938
and the people can enjoy the area while being underwater.

2436
01:36:48,939 --> 01:36:51,709
But people dance on the boat.

2437
01:36:51,939 --> 01:36:55,849
- Club music is played.
- Really?

2438
01:36:57,379 --> 01:36:58,379
What do we do?

2439
01:36:59,319 --> 01:37:00,588
(Chuckling)

2440
01:37:00,589 --> 01:37:03,088
The one that I saw was like that.

2441
01:37:03,089 --> 01:37:04,619
What did you just read? Tell us.

2442
01:37:05,159 --> 01:37:07,189
- It's similar to what she said. - Oh, my gosh.

2443
01:37:07,659 --> 01:37:09,488
It's a tour to see turtles and dolphins.

2444
01:37:09,489 --> 01:37:10,498
(Gemini's description is just like what Hye Yoon said.)

2445
01:37:10,499 --> 01:37:12,899
- People dance on the boat. - They dance?

2446
01:37:13,199 --> 01:37:14,368
- They dance? - People dance on the boat.

2447
01:37:14,369 --> 01:37:15,968
(They dance on the boat?)

2448
01:37:15,969 --> 01:37:17,169
With their rash guards on?

2449
01:37:18,639 --> 01:37:21,069
How are we supposed to dance with the turtles?

2450
01:37:21,409 --> 01:37:22,538
My gosh.

2451
01:37:22,539 --> 01:37:23,738
Like this with a dress on.

2452
01:37:23,739 --> 01:37:24,878
What's with those moves?

2453
01:37:24,879 --> 01:37:26,239
- Just like this. - What's with him?

2454
01:37:26,439 --> 01:37:28,409
He's practicing to dance with the turtles tomorrow.

2455
01:37:29,079 --> 01:37:32,749
I danced during my fanmeet event.

2456
01:37:34,249 --> 01:37:35,489
- What's with the way she talks? - And...

2457
01:37:35,989 --> 01:37:39,218
- That's the official way she talks. - It's so annoying.

2458
01:37:39,219 --> 01:37:40,729
Do you have a problem with that?

2459
01:37:40,829 --> 01:37:41,829
Right!

2460
01:37:41,959 --> 01:37:43,359
- So... - What did you dance to?

2461
01:37:43,659 --> 01:37:45,298
It was "NOT CUTE ANYMORE."

2462
01:37:45,299 --> 01:37:46,498
A song by ILLIT.

2463
01:37:46,499 --> 01:37:47,499
(Hye Yoon is working on ILLIT's song.)

2464
01:37:47,500 --> 01:37:48,669
It's that one.

2465
01:37:48,899 --> 01:37:51,399
I was watching my video,

2466
01:37:52,299 --> 01:37:54,139
and I wondered if I had some talent in dancing.

2467
01:37:54,369 --> 01:37:55,438
She's a great dancer.

2468
01:37:55,439 --> 01:37:57,069
- Really? - She has amazing moves.

2469
01:37:57,309 --> 01:37:58,438
She didn't look funny.

2470
01:37:58,439 --> 01:37:59,508
You speak like that,

2471
01:37:59,509 --> 01:38:01,149
- and you dance well as well? - Show us the video.

2472
01:38:01,749 --> 01:38:03,578
- Show us. - I know that song.

2473
01:38:03,579 --> 01:38:05,519
It's hard to believe.

2474
01:38:06,049 --> 01:38:10,049
You might not be able to find me because I'm too good.

2475
01:38:10,589 --> 01:38:12,719
- Was this released? - It wasn't released yet.

2476
01:38:13,489 --> 01:38:15,888
- Is she the one in the middle? - Look for me. Right.

2477
01:38:15,889 --> 01:38:17,129
- This one in white? - Right.

2478
01:38:17,929 --> 01:38:20,358
(Hye Yoon)

2479
01:38:20,359 --> 01:38:22,798
(Focused)

2480
01:38:22,799 --> 01:38:25,038
Gosh, look at her! She's just like Park Nam Jung.

2481
01:38:25,039 --> 01:38:26,799
- Gosh! - "Look at her."

2482
01:38:29,509 --> 01:38:31,239
- Gosh! - Gosh!

2483
01:38:31,479 --> 01:38:33,638
- What was that? - Gosh!

2484
01:38:33,639 --> 01:38:35,279
(They're like parents watching their child's talent show.)

2485
01:38:42,519 --> 01:38:44,219
Are you sick, Jun Myun?

2486
01:38:45,889 --> 01:38:47,458
This is a song I like.

2487
01:38:47,459 --> 01:38:50,089
We should wake up at 6am if it's at 7:10am.

2488
01:38:50,759 --> 01:38:52,729
We have to dance with the turtles.

2489
01:38:52,929 --> 01:38:54,499
- See you tomorrow! - Okay!

2490
01:38:54,799 --> 01:38:56,669
Don't worry and head inside.

2491
01:38:58,039 --> 01:39:01,209
(They turn off the lights one by one.)

2492
01:39:01,909 --> 01:39:04,179
(The four siblings experience the first night in the Philippines.)

2493
01:39:05,239 --> 01:39:10,249
(The tiring first night comes to an end.)

2494
01:39:11,349 --> 01:39:15,619
(The morning of the start of their vacation has come.)

2495
01:39:16,449 --> 01:39:18,519
(Surprised)

2496
01:39:20,089 --> 01:39:24,059
(Jung Ah sleeps in as she seems to be tired.)

2497
01:39:25,199 --> 01:39:32,499
(The other siblings are fast asleep as well.)

2498
01:39:33,699 --> 01:39:35,369
(Twitching)

2499
01:39:35,969 --> 01:39:37,578
(Jun Myun wakes up at 6:15am.)

2500
01:39:37,579 --> 01:39:42,309
(She makes her bed as soon as she gets up.)

2501
01:39:43,209 --> 01:39:46,919
(She gets changed into the perfect turtle outfit.)

2502
01:39:47,689 --> 01:39:49,649
Gosh, I feel so tired.

2503
01:39:49,789 --> 01:39:50,859
Me too.

2504
01:39:54,389 --> 01:39:57,998
(She relieves her fatigue from yesterday through stretching.)

2505
01:39:57,999 --> 01:40:01,029
(Groaning)

2506
01:40:01,729 --> 01:40:04,139
(Her short stretching session comes to an end.)

2507
01:40:04,439 --> 01:40:06,969
(Passing out)

2508
01:40:08,809 --> 01:40:13,839
(The aftereffect of work hits Jung Ah belatedly.)

2509
01:40:17,549 --> 01:40:22,349
(This person is quite diligent in the morning.)

2510
01:40:25,289 --> 01:40:27,089
(Surprised)

2511
01:40:27,429 --> 01:40:28,559
The mango pit from yesterday.

2512
01:40:29,329 --> 01:40:30,658
That's the pit?

2513
01:40:30,659 --> 01:40:32,729
(She can't let go of the mango even while explaining herself.)

2514
01:40:32,929 --> 01:40:34,929
- The pits? I'll suck on them. - The pits.

2515
01:40:35,299 --> 01:40:36,329
I'm not that person yet.

2516
01:40:37,639 --> 01:40:40,369
(She keeps her word well.)

2517
01:40:41,469 --> 01:40:42,469
Have some of the coffee.

2518
01:40:42,470 --> 01:40:45,209
(The sisters share the coffee.)

2519
01:40:45,639 --> 01:40:47,448
We're going to see the turtles.

2520
01:40:47,449 --> 01:40:50,109
I wonder how much I must doll myself up.

2521
01:40:51,019 --> 01:40:54,919
(This much)

2522
01:40:55,289 --> 01:40:58,189
You look so cute in purple, Hye Yoon.

2523
01:40:59,259 --> 01:41:01,629
I must take a picture of this. What's with you?

2524
01:41:01,789 --> 01:41:04,128
You're so cute. Stay right there. Let me take a photo of you.

2525
01:41:04,129 --> 01:41:05,129
(Photo Park has come all the way to the Philippines.)

2526
01:41:05,329 --> 01:41:06,329
Gosh, look at her legs.

2527
01:41:09,599 --> 01:41:13,069
(She's ready to meet the turtles.)

2528
01:41:13,299 --> 01:41:14,368
Kim Hye Yoon.

2529
01:41:14,369 --> 01:41:15,369
(She finds her to be cute.)

2530
01:41:15,370 --> 01:41:16,969
I had no choice. I had to take a photo of her.

2531
01:41:17,939 --> 01:41:19,478
(Dex comes in as the photos are taken.)

2532
01:41:19,479 --> 01:41:21,079
- Good morning! - Hey.

2533
01:41:22,409 --> 01:41:24,219
(Shall the siblings head out now?)

2534
01:41:25,049 --> 01:41:26,178
Hello.

2535
01:41:26,179 --> 01:41:27,179
(Hye Yoon comes out first in her purple swimwear.)

2536
01:41:27,589 --> 01:41:28,989
Hello.

2537
01:41:29,089 --> 01:41:30,118
(Mark was waiting outside.)

2538
01:41:30,119 --> 01:41:31,459
Good morning!

2539
01:41:32,019 --> 01:41:33,459
- Did you sleep well? - Yes.

2540
01:41:33,789 --> 01:41:35,528
(They give each other a morning hug.)

2541
01:41:35,529 --> 01:41:36,559
Let's set off.

2542
01:41:37,899 --> 01:41:41,268
(The four siblings get in the car.)

2543
01:41:41,269 --> 01:41:43,399
Are you okay now? Is your body much better now?

2544
01:41:43,769 --> 01:41:44,899
Does your body ache all over?

2545
01:41:45,499 --> 01:41:47,509
- I'm not aching as much. - Same here.

2546
01:41:48,209 --> 01:41:50,239
- I'm fine now. - We were so worried yesterday.

2547
01:41:50,439 --> 01:41:52,178
I feel a bit of muscle pain from my workout yesterday.

2548
01:41:52,179 --> 01:41:53,179
(Dex feels a bit of muscle pain.)

2549
01:41:53,180 --> 01:41:55,448
Why do you feel muscle pain when you work out all the time?

2550
01:41:55,449 --> 01:41:57,919
Did you work out after taking a break?

2551
01:41:58,049 --> 01:42:00,279
This means the workout was successful.

2552
01:42:00,479 --> 01:42:04,189
Muscles grow bigger as they recover from being torn.

2553
01:42:04,489 --> 01:42:06,189
Why tear up your muscles?

2554
01:42:06,559 --> 01:42:07,559
(She might be right about that.)

2555
01:42:07,560 --> 01:42:08,888
"Why tear up your muscles?"

2556
01:42:08,889 --> 01:42:09,889
(Her funny comment is said one more time.)

2557
01:42:10,999 --> 01:42:11,999
I'm feeling fine right now.

2558
01:42:12,000 --> 01:42:13,628
I can dance with the turtles.

2559
01:42:13,629 --> 01:42:16,098
Get ready. I'm going to put on a fantastic performance with them.

2560
01:42:16,099 --> 01:42:17,268
I'm ready to dance.

2561
01:42:17,269 --> 01:42:18,539
You're going to scare the turtles.

2562
01:42:20,809 --> 01:42:24,178
(After moving in the car while chatting and laughing,)

2563
01:42:24,179 --> 01:42:26,008
I slightly saw the sea.

2564
01:42:26,009 --> 01:42:27,608
(a refreshing scenery can be seen.)

2565
01:42:27,609 --> 01:42:28,909
It's the sea!

2566
01:42:30,409 --> 01:42:33,519
(The sun's glitter feels so bright.)

2567
01:42:36,719 --> 01:42:39,389
(The bottom can be seen from the clear sea.)

2568
01:42:40,059 --> 01:42:42,629
(There's a beautiful white beach as well.)

2569
01:42:45,929 --> 01:42:47,729
(The real vacation in Bohol begins.)

2570
01:42:48,929 --> 01:42:49,969
(Amazed)

2571
01:42:53,299 --> 01:42:54,909
It feels different here.

2572
01:42:55,809 --> 01:42:56,839
Gosh!

2573
01:42:57,169 --> 01:42:58,209
This is awesome.

2574
01:42:58,339 --> 01:42:59,809
(Amazed)

2575
01:43:00,849 --> 01:43:03,809
Where are the turtles? The turtles.

2576
01:43:05,379 --> 01:43:09,189
(Shall we head out to the sea to meet the turtles?)

2577
01:43:10,749 --> 01:43:13,289
Can we dance with the turtles if we move this way?

2578
01:43:15,059 --> 01:43:16,858
You must get on the boat.

2579
01:43:16,859 --> 01:43:18,499
(You must get on the boat to meet the turtles.)

2580
01:43:19,399 --> 01:43:21,568
- Hello. - Hello.

2581
01:43:21,569 --> 01:43:22,569
(Today's dance mates)

2582
01:43:22,899 --> 01:43:24,069
Thank you.

2583
01:43:24,569 --> 01:43:26,768
Hello, everyone. It's a pleasure to meet you all.

2584
01:43:26,769 --> 01:43:29,309
- Hello. - Hello. This is Dex.

2585
01:43:29,869 --> 01:43:33,909
(Bring up the atmosphere.)

2586
01:43:34,549 --> 01:43:35,779
(Please take your seat.)

2587
01:43:36,079 --> 01:43:39,049
(Why must I feel embarrassed for him?)

2588
01:43:40,379 --> 01:43:41,388
(He gets stopped right away.)

2589
01:43:41,389 --> 01:43:42,918
- Please stay seated. - Oh, right.

2590
01:43:42,919 --> 01:43:44,458
One, two, three.

2591
01:43:44,459 --> 01:43:47,628
(The crew members push the boat to help the boat sail off.)

2592
01:43:47,629 --> 01:43:51,258
Who was the one to eat so much last night?

2593
01:43:51,259 --> 01:43:52,329
(Laughing)

2594
01:43:52,759 --> 01:43:55,129
(They manage to set off.)

2595
01:43:55,869 --> 01:43:57,839
(Where are the four siblings headed to?)

2596
01:43:58,199 --> 01:43:59,938
It was very cloudy today.

2597
01:43:59,939 --> 01:44:01,939
I think the skies have opened up for all of you today.

2598
01:44:02,839 --> 01:44:05,838
We will transfer to a bigger boat after moving for five minutes.

2599
01:44:05,839 --> 01:44:08,648
The first thing we'll do is to meet the dolphins.

2600
01:44:08,649 --> 01:44:11,049
- Dolphins? - We'll meet the dolphins first.

2601
01:44:11,219 --> 01:44:13,119
We'll swim with the turtles after that.

2602
01:44:14,119 --> 01:44:15,519
(A tour)

2603
01:44:17,449 --> 01:44:19,188
(Today...)

2604
01:44:19,189 --> 01:44:21,888
(it's Dance with Turtles.)

2605
01:44:21,889 --> 01:44:24,459
(Hopping tour)

2606
01:44:25,399 --> 01:44:28,499
(Once you dive into the water,)

2607
01:44:28,969 --> 01:44:33,569
(a whole new world of Bohol unfolds before you.)

2608
01:44:34,509 --> 01:44:39,909
(Wonderful coral reefs and colorful fishes)

2609
01:44:40,339 --> 01:44:43,109
(In this beautiful sea,)

2610
01:44:44,149 --> 01:44:48,549
(will they be able to meet dolphins and wild turtles?)

2611
01:44:49,189 --> 01:44:51,358
("Dance with Turtles" was the hopping tour.)

2612
01:44:51,359 --> 01:44:52,558
Did you all have breakfast?

2613
01:44:52,559 --> 01:44:54,019
- No. - No?

2614
01:44:54,359 --> 01:44:55,689
You will be served with mangoes first.

2615
01:44:56,389 --> 01:44:58,298
(Mangoes?)

2616
01:44:58,299 --> 01:44:59,559
I love mangoes.

2617
01:44:59,629 --> 01:45:00,829
- You do? - Yes.

2618
01:45:01,129 --> 01:45:03,129
She eats four mangoes at once.

2619
01:45:04,029 --> 01:45:05,198
(Four?)

2620
01:45:05,199 --> 01:45:06,938
There's enough for each person to have five.

2621
01:45:06,939 --> 01:45:08,569
Right. Please give us a lot.

2622
01:45:09,269 --> 01:45:10,839
I'm going to dance after eating the mangoes.

2623
01:45:11,479 --> 01:45:16,209
(They are heading toward the mango party boat.)

2624
01:45:16,349 --> 01:45:18,119
There's our boat. They're waving at us.

2625
01:45:19,179 --> 01:45:20,179
Really?

2626
01:45:20,180 --> 01:45:22,419
(Our mango party boat?)

2627
01:45:31,859 --> 01:45:33,159
(Surprised)

2628
01:45:33,829 --> 01:45:34,898
(He grasps his head.)

2629
01:45:34,899 --> 01:45:38,039
(Why did the siblings get surprised?)

2630
01:45:41,609 --> 01:45:43,239
(It's such a big welcome.)

2631
01:45:44,009 --> 01:45:48,879
(The greeting dance is getting wilder.)

2632
01:45:49,409 --> 01:45:51,248
(Oh, dear.)

2633
01:45:51,249 --> 01:45:52,419
Their energy is making me feel shy.

2634
01:45:53,179 --> 01:45:54,849
(Covering her mouth)

2635
01:45:55,089 --> 01:45:59,489
(At a loss for words at the unexpected energy)

2636
01:45:59,789 --> 01:46:00,918
(This is bad.)

2637
01:46:00,919 --> 01:46:03,958
What you did just now was nothing.

2638
01:46:03,959 --> 01:46:05,229
(I wasn't hoping for this much energy.)

2639
01:46:05,859 --> 01:46:09,329
(Regardless, they're very hyped up.)

2640
01:46:09,829 --> 01:46:12,999
(They're getting more energetic.)

2641
01:46:13,499 --> 01:46:15,639
(They've barely started.)

2642
01:46:15,809 --> 01:46:17,439
(Welcome.)

2643
01:46:18,439 --> 01:46:19,709
Is this really happening?

2644
01:46:20,379 --> 01:46:22,149
They maintain that energy for six hours.

2645
01:46:22,379 --> 01:46:23,509
Six hours?

2646
01:46:24,619 --> 01:46:26,519
(Shocked)

2647
01:46:26,819 --> 01:46:28,089
They're way too hyped.

2648
01:46:29,219 --> 01:46:34,788
(Can the siblings survive in the dance nightmare?)

2649
01:46:34,789 --> 01:46:36,889
One, two, three.

2650
01:46:37,329 --> 01:46:38,899
- Hello! - Hello!

2651
01:46:39,759 --> 01:46:43,028
(They enter the energetic course.)

2652
01:46:43,029 --> 01:46:45,468
- Hello. - Hello.

2653
01:46:45,469 --> 01:46:48,008
(They're changing to a bigger boat.)

2654
01:46:48,009 --> 01:46:49,408
At 8am in the morning.

2655
01:46:49,409 --> 01:46:51,509
- Hello. - We're in trouble.

2656
01:46:52,539 --> 01:46:53,579
(Moaning)

2657
01:46:54,139 --> 01:46:58,519
(The welcome ceremony hasn't ended yet.)

2658
01:46:59,279 --> 01:47:01,489
(The crew welcomes them passionately.)

2659
01:47:01,789 --> 01:47:04,049
(It's nice to meet you.)

2660
01:47:04,389 --> 01:47:06,159
(Welcome.)

2661
01:47:06,519 --> 01:47:08,829
(The 1st crisis in his 8 years of life)

2662
01:47:09,629 --> 01:47:11,499
(The siblings have never experienced such a welcome ceremony either.)

2663
01:47:12,929 --> 01:47:14,259
They perform for you.

2664
01:47:15,999 --> 01:47:18,739
(A welcome dance)

2665
01:47:19,239 --> 01:47:21,969
(I like a performance.)

2666
01:47:22,239 --> 01:47:26,309
(Preheating the excitement)

2667
01:47:26,809 --> 01:47:29,848
(He's slowly getting engrossed.)

2668
01:47:29,849 --> 01:47:30,879
Yes.

2669
01:47:31,219 --> 01:47:33,579
(Impressive stunts follow.)

2670
01:47:34,019 --> 01:47:35,818
(Eyes wide open)

2671
01:47:35,819 --> 01:47:36,819
Amazing.

2672
01:47:38,719 --> 01:47:42,289
(From breakdancing...)

2673
01:47:42,829 --> 01:47:45,959
(to acrobatics)

2674
01:47:46,559 --> 01:47:48,529
(What did I just see?)

2675
01:47:49,499 --> 01:47:50,499
(Flying)

2676
01:47:55,069 --> 01:47:56,539
(Sliding down)

2677
01:47:57,339 --> 01:47:59,708
(She's beat even before seeing a turtle.)

2678
01:47:59,709 --> 01:48:00,839
This is bad.

2679
01:48:01,579 --> 01:48:02,678
It's fun.

2680
01:48:02,679 --> 01:48:03,749
- Really? - Yes.

2681
01:48:04,349 --> 01:48:06,119
We don't dance with turtles.

2682
01:48:06,279 --> 01:48:07,718
We see turtles, and we dance.

2683
01:48:07,719 --> 01:48:09,088
- I think so too. - Together.

2684
01:48:09,089 --> 01:48:11,519
We dance and see turtles.

2685
01:48:11,719 --> 01:48:12,959
I want to see turtles.

2686
01:48:14,219 --> 01:48:19,329
(We're getting closer to turtles.)

2687
01:48:20,129 --> 01:48:22,729
- Isn't the weather fantastic? - Yes, the weather is nice.

2688
01:48:23,099 --> 01:48:24,398
(Absorbing the weather)

2689
01:48:24,399 --> 01:48:25,638
My gosh.

2690
01:48:25,639 --> 01:48:29,369
The sun isn't too strong. It's perfect.

2691
01:48:29,669 --> 01:48:31,908
The wind is breezy.

2692
01:48:31,909 --> 01:48:33,308
(The perfect weather for a hopping tour)

2693
01:48:33,309 --> 01:48:34,439
It's so nice.

2694
01:48:35,009 --> 01:48:38,979
In 2 to 3 minutes, we'll arrive at the dolphin area.

2695
01:48:39,849 --> 01:48:41,248
It's my first time seeing dolphins.

2696
01:48:41,249 --> 01:48:42,249
Really?

2697
01:48:42,619 --> 01:48:44,288
It's my first time seeing one at the sea.

2698
01:48:44,289 --> 01:48:46,419
- Right, at the sea. - Yes.

2699
01:48:46,859 --> 01:48:49,159
You don't get to see them up close.

2700
01:48:50,129 --> 01:48:54,799
(How will the dolphins greet us?)

2701
01:48:55,169 --> 01:48:59,969
(The boat sails nonstop to the dolphin area.)

2702
01:49:00,639 --> 01:49:03,069
(They've finally arrived.)

2703
01:49:03,669 --> 01:49:06,539
All the other boats have gathered here.

2704
01:49:07,009 --> 01:49:08,079
You're right.

2705
01:49:09,709 --> 01:49:15,519
(The sea is still silent.)

2706
01:49:16,089 --> 01:49:19,859
(They wait nervously.)

2707
01:49:20,319 --> 01:49:21,729
Why won't they come out?

2708
01:49:22,159 --> 01:49:23,529
(Dolphins, let us meet quickly.)

2709
01:49:23,789 --> 01:49:26,299
(Is it not time yet?)

2710
01:49:27,799 --> 01:49:29,899
- There! - What?

2711
01:49:29,999 --> 01:49:31,699
(Could it be?)

2712
01:49:32,639 --> 01:49:36,369
(Something's there!)

2713
01:49:36,839 --> 01:49:40,679
(Surprised)

2714
01:49:44,619 --> 01:49:46,279
There they are. Can you see?

2715
01:49:46,619 --> 01:49:47,648
Yes.

2716
01:49:47,649 --> 01:49:51,219
(The dolphins finally show themselves.)

2717
01:49:53,489 --> 01:49:55,729
- My gosh. - Nice.

2718
01:49:56,729 --> 01:49:58,029
Look over there.

2719
01:49:59,599 --> 01:50:00,629
Goodness.

2720
01:50:03,929 --> 01:50:06,799
(Swimming powerfully)

2721
01:50:10,269 --> 01:50:11,839
There are so many of them.

2722
01:50:12,109 --> 01:50:14,309
- There are a lot of dolphins. - Right? There are so many.

2723
01:50:16,909 --> 01:50:21,819
(They swim across the blue sea and say hi.)

2724
01:50:25,489 --> 01:50:32,429
(This is how they look in the water.)

2725
01:50:33,599 --> 01:50:38,439
(The dolphins move beautifully.)

2726
01:50:42,239 --> 01:50:44,539
(They just observe in a daze.)

2727
01:50:46,139 --> 01:50:48,048
(They try to capture every dolphin with their eyes.)

2728
01:50:48,049 --> 01:50:49,049
So cute.

2729
01:50:50,349 --> 01:50:54,549
(They do a welcoming stunt too.)

2730
01:50:56,119 --> 01:50:57,148
So cute.

2731
01:50:57,149 --> 01:50:58,518
(The happiest person right now)

2732
01:50:58,519 --> 01:50:59,559
They're so cute.

2733
01:51:00,059 --> 01:51:01,118
Jump!

2734
01:51:01,119 --> 01:51:02,459
(Dolphin, jump one more time!)

2735
01:51:02,829 --> 01:51:04,389
(Laughing)

2736
01:51:04,829 --> 01:51:06,828
Are you embarrassed? Are you?

2737
01:51:06,829 --> 01:51:08,098
- Kim Hye Yoon. - No.

2738
01:51:08,099 --> 01:51:09,768
- Can't you see I'm doing my best? - How could I...

2739
01:51:09,769 --> 01:51:11,229
be embarrassed by you?

2740
01:51:11,969 --> 01:51:15,539
(Looking at the beautiful dolphins makes their happiness level rise.)

2741
01:51:17,909 --> 01:51:20,679
(As if to meet their expectations, they jump again.)

2742
01:51:22,979 --> 01:51:24,548
(Are they saying hi to us?)

2743
01:51:24,549 --> 01:51:25,649
A baby dolphin.

2744
01:51:27,149 --> 01:51:29,589
- How cute. - This is fascinating.

2745
01:51:30,349 --> 01:51:35,458
(Everyone here will remember this moment forever.)

2746
01:51:35,459 --> 01:51:36,529
It's a dolphin!

2747
01:51:38,199 --> 01:51:41,299
(She's happy.)

2748
01:51:56,409 --> 01:52:00,019
(Since we met the dolphins, let's go dance with turtles!)

2749
01:52:00,196 --> 01:52:01,296
(Shouting)

2750
01:52:01,736 --> 01:52:02,806
(What is this?)

2751
01:52:03,466 --> 01:52:05,836
(Welcome to the 1st row of a water festival.)

2752
01:52:06,206 --> 01:52:07,735
(The nightmare of energy starts again.)

2753
01:52:07,736 --> 01:52:09,146
(Clenching her eyes)

2754
01:52:09,676 --> 01:52:10,946
(Crying out)

2755
01:52:11,046 --> 01:52:12,076
(I'm totally drained!)

2756
01:52:12,416 --> 01:52:13,716
(This isn't right.)

2757
01:52:14,116 --> 01:52:16,545
(Their vacation turns into survival in an instant.)

2758
01:52:16,546 --> 01:52:17,815
(Drop the anchor now!)

2759
01:52:17,816 --> 01:52:19,185
(The final dance)

2760
01:52:19,186 --> 01:52:20,186
(Gosh, stop it now!)

2761
01:52:20,556 --> 01:52:21,656
(Can we see turtles at this rate?)

2762
01:52:21,926 --> 01:52:24,755
(Will the plan to meet wild turtles go up in smoke?)

2763
01:52:24,756 --> 01:52:26,226
(The four siblings are completely exhausted.)

2764
01:52:26,856 --> 01:52:28,126
(I can't even go back and cook!)

2765
01:52:28,726 --> 01:52:30,396
(For the first time on the show, they go on a dinner strike?)

2766
01:52:30,796 --> 01:52:32,735
(The kitchen is closed today.)

2767
01:52:32,736 --> 01:52:34,166
(The reality hits her.)

2768
01:52:34,596 --> 01:52:35,906
(Let's go, please.)

2769
01:52:36,306 --> 01:52:38,206
(Glancing)

2770
01:52:38,676 --> 01:52:40,106
(Francis?)

2771
01:52:40,206 --> 01:52:41,776
("Men in Black?")

2772
01:52:42,006 --> 01:52:43,646
(And elegant actresses)

2773
01:52:44,206 --> 01:52:46,446
(What's the mysterious night out about?)

2774
01:52:46,676 --> 01:52:48,246
(And...)

2775
01:52:48,946 --> 01:52:49,946
(It's a winding mountain road.)

2776
01:52:49,947 --> 01:52:51,416
(I have a bad feeling about this.)

2777
01:52:51,786 --> 01:52:52,915
(They arrive at a mysterious workplace...)

2778
01:52:52,916 --> 01:52:54,286
(after driving up the mountain for one hour.)

2779
01:52:54,416 --> 01:52:56,426
(What unfolds in front of the four nervous siblings...)

2780
01:52:56,786 --> 01:53:00,196
(is an expansive field about 33,100m² big.)

2781
01:53:00,526 --> 01:53:01,625
(Harvest everything...)

2782
01:53:01,626 --> 01:53:03,996
(that grows on this field.)

2783
01:53:04,266 --> 01:53:07,066
(We need to go around the whole field?)

2784
01:53:07,296 --> 01:53:09,035
(In the wildest wild...)

2785
01:53:09,036 --> 01:53:10,406
(of the show's history,)

2786
01:53:10,536 --> 01:53:12,906
(the four siblings collapse in the end?)

2787
01:53:13,376 --> 01:53:16,976
(Will they be able to survive?)
